<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5064902>
    dc:description "FIGURES 35–37. Phthinomita jonesi n. sp. from the intertrabecular spaces of the ventricle (heart) of Siganus lineatus off Lizard Island. 35. Adult. Dorsal anteriorly, twisting laterally at level of “arrow a”, ventral side to the left, whole mount. 36. Male terminal genitalia, dorsal view. 37. Female terminal genitalia, lateral view. Scale­bars: 35,37, 250 m; 36, 100 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5064902/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

